  
                    
                        
                
                
            Chelsea midfielder N'Golo Kante has signed a new five-year deal to keep him at the club until 2023.The France international has scored three goals in 81 Premier League appearances for the Blues after joining from Leicester City in 2016.Kante helped the club to the Premier League title in his first season at Stamford Bridge.
    
        
"It has been two beautiful years and I wish for more to come," said the 27-year-old."Since I came, I completely improved as a player, challenged myself and got some awards I never thought about."I like the city, I like the club and I am happy to be here for more time."More to follow.
 
